declare_parcel_as_script_with_stdin <<'-/-'
Define integer constant globals.
-/-

# ....................{ BOOLEANS                           }....................
declare_global_with_stdin <<'/---'
boolean ZESHY_BOOLEAN_FALSE

Arbitrary string signifying a boolean false value. Since `zsh` supports no
boolean type, we emulate such type with string constants.
/---
ZESHY_BOOLEAN_FALSE=

declare_global_with_stdin <<'/---'
boolean ZESHY_BOOLEAN_TRUE

Arbitrary string signifying a boolean true value. Since `zsh` supports no
boolean type, we emulate such type with string constants.
/---
ZESHY_BOOLEAN_TRUE='true'

# --------------------( WASTELANDS                         )--------------------
